# MernCrest Part 03 — Customer Portal

Continue from Part 01. Do not redesign or remove modules.

## Portal role

The Customer Portal is the customer’s complete self-service dashboard.

- Unique profile per customer (`customerCode`)
- Purchased services appear automatically after provider activation
- Dashboard must surface: welcome, profile, orders, services, invoices, tickets, announcements, notifications, renewals, pending payments, quick actions, activity

## Reseller (unchanged)

```text
Customer → MernCrest Marketplace → Provider API → Service Activated
```

Never hardcode a single provider. Prefer priority-ordered active providers.

## CRM integration rule

Customer events (register, order, ticket, payment submit) MUST update:

- Portal `CustomerActivity`
- CRM lead/activity
- Portal notifications where relevant

## Payments

Manual / bank transfer → pending → admin verification. Gateways remain future-ready.

## Quality

Reusable modules · no duplicated business logic · validate APIs · enterprise quality only.
Integrate with CRM, Finance, Support, Analytics, Notifications, Reports, Audit Logs.
